2 Invocation
************

The synopsis to invoke Qi is:

     qi <command> [options] [package|recipe|order] ...

The following commands are supported by `qi':

`install'
     Install packages to the system (.tlz).

`remove'
     Remove packages of the system.

`erupt'
     Examine packages for debugging purposes.

`order'
     Resolves the build order through .order files.

`build'
     Build packages using recipe files.


     There are global or common options for the commands, as well as
     specific to each one.


     *Global options:*

`-h'
     Show options for the given command and exit.

`-N'
     Don't read runtime configuration file `qirc'.


     *Options for command `install':*

`-P'
     Package installation tree.

     This option sets `${packagedir}'.

     The default value for *packagedir* is /usr/packages.

`-T'
     Target directory for linking.

     This option sets `${targetdir}'.

     The default value for *targetdir* is /.

`-p'
     Prune conflicts.

`-r'
     Read package from the named pipe.

`-v'
     graft(1) verbosity (use -V instead for more verbosity).

`-w'
     Warn about the files that will be linked.


     *Options for command `remove':*

`-P'
     Package (de)installation tree.

     This option sets `${packagedir}'.

     The default value for *packagedir* is /usr/packages.

`-T'
     Target directory for unlinking.

     This option sets `${targetdir}'.

     The default value for *targetdir* is /.

`-k'
     Keep (don't delete) the package directory.

`-n'
     Non-interactive mode.

`-p'
     Prune conflicts.

`-v'
     graft(1) verbosity (use -V instead for more verbosity).


     *Options for command `build':*

`-C'
     Create named pipe for communicate package name.

`-S'
     Don't strip unneeded or debugging symbols from files.

     This option sets `${strip}'.

     The default value for *strip* is strip.

`-k'
     Keep (don't delete) `${srcdir}' and `${destdir}' after the build.

`-n'
     Don't create a .tlz package.

`-o'
     Where the produced packages are written.

     This option sets `${outdir}'.

     The default value for *outdir* is /var/cache/qi/packages.

`-t'
     Temporary directory for compilation.

     This option sets `${tmpdir}'.

     The default value for *tmpdir* is /tmp/sources.

`-w'
     Working directory tree for archive, patches, recipes.

     This option sets `${worktree}'.

     The default value for *worktree* is /usr/src/qi.

`-z'
     Where to find the compressed sources.

     This option sets `${tardir}'.

     The default value for *tardir* is /usr/src/qi/sources.

`-a'
     Architecture to use.

     This option sets `${arch}'.

     The default value is obtained via uname(1): `uname -m'.

`-i'
     Increment release number when a package is produced.

`-j'
     Parallel jobs for the compiler

     This option sets `${jobs}'.

     The default value for *jobs* is 1.


     *Options for command `erupt':*

`-d'
     Decompression directory.

     If not specified, the default value is the Current Working
     Directory.


   * All the options can be mixed.

Notes:

   Options specified in the command-line have priority over the config
file: `qirc'.  If there are no options, and if `qirc' is not present,
default (internal) values will be used instead.

2.1 Help Actions
================

There are several levels of help in which the help is showed.  If `qi'
is invoked without arguments, then the general help appears.  Which is
also equivalent to `qi help'.

   Type `qi help <command>' for more information on a specific command.

If the help does not appear when a command is invoked without
arguments, please use `qi <command> -h'.


