6 Examine packages
******************

*erupt* is a special command to examine packages for debugging purposes:

_Usage:_ qi install [-h] [-d <dir>] package.tlz

   * This is equivalent to the shell instruction:

     `( umask 000 ; cd directory/ && tar -xvf package.tlz )'

     The permissions are set to "u=rwx,g=rwx,o=rwx" and the package
     content is decompressed inside a directory.

   * The specified package must be a regular file.

   * Only one package can be passed per-invocation.

   * A pre-existing directory is required to operate.

   * If you don't provide a different directory name using the -d
     option, the package is decompressed in the Current Working
     Directory.  The root directory (/) cannot be used for these
     purposes.

If you make some changes to the directory where the package is
decompressed, and has in mind to repackage.  We suggest increase the
build number of the package.


